He figured the soreness was normal and later in the evening on 30Mar2021, the pain became an issue when he tried to go to bed that evening. Since the first two nights compared to last night, the soreness is actually improved; every time he tries to sleep with pain as a factor it is not easy. The patient can feel throbbing with his heartbeat and with the circulation there is throbbing pain. The pain was terrible and was throbbing like his heartbeat and similar to like a shoulder rotator cuff injury. For the first two days, on Tuesday (30Mar2021) and Wednesday (31Mar2021) after the vaccine, he could not use his arm or lift his arm above his mid face level. According to the patient, it was like a rotator cuff and he had a torn rotator cuff 15 to 20 years ago and this is the same arm that his torn rotator cuff occurred in; this is very painful and he is comparing it to the torn rotator cuff. In Mar2021, the patient had burning and tingling down the left arm and 3 days no sleep because the pain is worse at night. During the last week (Mar2021), his left leg down to his foot is also tingling and burning. The patient's primary care physician just retired, and he is in the process of finding a new one. The patient had no treatment or physician or emergency room (ER) visit for the reported events because being in the ER field, he can tell right now that it would be a waste of time of the effort to go into the ER as they would do nothing but tell him to take paracetamol (TYLENOL) and that is it. The patient did not like to take paracetamol and hates taking paracetamol. The patient clarified it is generic acetaminophen extra strength (Strength: 500 mg; Lot Number: P119682, Expiration Date: Mar2022, UPC Number: 5084417594) that he has taken (maybe every 6 hours oral) and it does relieve the pain so that is only so good. He does not know if in motion of the course of the day, something happened because at night laying still in bed is when he has pain. The patient did a lot of research before he made this call and the severity of the pain is enough to actually keep him awake for three days. He thought it was severe pain; maybe he should have told them to administer the vaccine in his right arm, but it was administered into his left arm. The only reason he made this call was because he wanted someone to know what he was having which could be just completely normal and he is sure every reaction is different and he expected the soreness because he remembers as a kid having shots. Also, this level of pain he is experiencing is what he wanted to report; imagine having  himself going three days without a full night of sleep and he wanted to report this to make sure Pfizer knew this if they were keeping track of numbers of how many people have a similar pain level. The patient also asked if there were other people who called and reported these symptoms and if there is any information or treatment recommendations. As of 08Apr2021, even up to five days after getting the shot, now going on seven days that he has had some pretty severe reactions. The patient called in after 3 nights of getting no sleep. The patient was calling today to see if someone was ever going to call him back and asking will there be a follow up call from someone to see if he's still alive. The patient had some pretty severe reactions and they have actually gotten worse. There also have been new developments. The patient had pain in his arm that pulses along with his heart rate. It is so bad that it kept him up for 3 nights and still wakes him up at night. The pulsing pain in his arm started on the first night and has gradually gotten worse. The pain in the arm that is enough that it keeps him awake at night only starts getting severe when he goes to bed. He has tried sleeping in an upright position and he has tried everything, and nothing seems to alleviate it. The patient took generic acetaminophen which did not work during his last phone call. The patient also tried naproxen sodium (ALEVE) and that doesn't work wither. It was absolutely debilitating at times to where he has a 50% deficit with the use of his left arm (Mar2021). The patient was having second thoughts about getting the second shot. People in the medical field have told him there is thin line now to treat side effects because of liability; some doctors won't even get into it, just refer to Pfizer because medical insurance will not cover any services related to COVID-19 vaccine reactions. The patient continues to explain that is why the federal government is the only one that owns the shot due to liability. The patient's main concern is calling and reporting and maybe getting some help in deciding whether or not to get the second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. In his opinion, that is too long to have pain that he cannot sleep, the pain wakes him up. This all happened along with the shot, the same night and there are times where he can't work due to it. The patient asks if anyone is concerned with it and will someone feel bad because he doesn't get the second shot. His main concern is that people are underscoring or even lying about side effects, stating he can't believe he is an isolated case. The patient continued to ask if this is something he's stuck with, or if it is something he would have to deal with from now on from getting this shot. The patient regrets getting the first shot and stated that if he knew then what he would be going through now, he wouldn't have got it. The patient has no sort of history of being a hypochondriac and the feelings he is going through right now are sensations that he has never felt in his life. The patient continues to explain he doesn't even know how to categorize it other than mentally relating it to the shot since it all occurred in line with Mar2021 getting the shot. The patient further commented that if he ran a call with an ambulance right now with a patient telling him what i he was telling the company, he wouldn't even know what to do with them other than getting them comfortable and to a hospital. The patient had not recovered from "Soreness on the around the shot site", "Severe arm pain up where the rotator cuff is", and " Has not slept due to pain; cannot sleep, the pain wakes him up". Concomitant medication included levothyroxine sodium (SYNTHROID) taken for thyroid therapy from 1977 to an unspecified stop date. After the first vaccine she broke out in a rash, and after the second vaccine she broke out in another rash which was worse. She still has it in the neck area. She put Cortisone lotion on it and it goes away and comes back. She usually uses the size of a dime or a quarter. She also broke out in Shingles. It's clear across her back. She was still itchy. After the second injection she was itching all over her head, hands, arms, legs, and feet. She was reading about the side effects of a rash, but her whole body was itching. She broke out in shingles and she never had that before. She needs to get Temlos injections for her osteoporosis, she was supposed to start, but she refrained from doing so because she was afraid it might affect the COVID vaccine or the COVID vaccine will affect these injections. The second injection made the 2-inch slough on her arm from the first dose worse, but it went away faster. She also got a 2-inch slough on her neck and she still have it. That was what she was concerned about. The one on her neck came back in a flurry after the second injection, and that was when she broke out in shingles, it blew up like fire on back and neck. Its drying up. The one neck was flaring, red, itching and dry. She put Cortisone lotion on it. Her lower back still has the rash. Injection site hurts; arm feels like black and blue but its not; This is a spontaneous report received from contactable consumer (patient) from a Pfizer sponsored program. A female patient of an unspecified age received BNT162B2 (BNT162B2; PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; Lot number and expiry date not reported), via an unspecified route of administration, on 04May2021, 1ST DOSE, SINGLE for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. On an unspecified date in May2021, after she received her first dose, her arm felt like black and blue but it is not (as reported) and injection site hurts a little. The provider asked the patient when she wanted to receive the second dose and the patient picked 19May2021 (2 weeks). The patient read the fact sheet that the facility gave her after receiving the 1st dose and she had read that the 2nd dose should be given 3 weeks after the 1st dose hence the patient rescheduled her second dose. The outcome of the events was not recovered.  No follow up attempts are possible. Information on lot/batch number cannot be obtained.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: dizzy spell; Spinning feeling of heat from her feet to her head; stomach pains/stomach hurts when eating; stomach muscle spasms; possible weight gain; feels cold all the time; easy bruising; This is a spontaneous report from a non-contactable consumer (patient). The patient experienced dizzy spell, felt like spinning feeling of heat from her feet to her head day after COVID vaccine on an unspecified date. The patient had stomach pain/stomach hurts when eating and stomach muscle spasms, possible weight gain, feels cold all the time and easy bruising on an unspecified date. The outcome was unknown at the reporting time.   No follow-up attempts are needed; information about lot/batch number cannot be obtained.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Not feeling well; fatigued; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (who reported for herself) . A 29-year-old female patient received the first dose of BNT162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE; Batch/Lot number EW0150) on 30Mar2021 at 11:30 AM, via an unspecified route of administration on an unspecified date as a single dose for covid-19 immunization, in left arm. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. Prior to vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19. Medical history was not reported. The patient had no known allergies. Concomitant medications included: Birth control. On 03Mar2021 at 05:00 PM, the patient experienced she was "not feeling well" she means that she was fatigued and beat all the time. Reporter stated this event started within the first 24 hours of being administered the first dose but that now she is almost 100% recovered from feeling fatigued and feeling beat. The clinical outcome of the events was recovered.  Since the vaccination, the patient has not been tested for COVID-19.   Information on lot/ batch number has been requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: significant headache; tested positive of COVID-19; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (physician Assistant) reporting for her husband.   A male patient of an unspecified age received bnt162b2 (BNT162B2), dose 1 via an unspecified route of administration on 22Apr2021 (Batch/Lot number was not reported) as single dose at an unknown age for COVID-19 immunisation.  The patient medical history and concomitant medications were not reported.  The patient was tested positive of COVID-19 in Apr2021 after vaccination, significant headache on 22Apr2021. The event tested positive of COVID-19 was considered medically significant. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included Sars-cov-2 test: positive in Apr2021, his test results (both rapid and PCR) confirmed positive. The course of events was as follows: her husband received his first dose of the Pfizer vaccine Thursday 22Apr2021 and developed a significant headache. Friday a.m. 23Apr2021 as he still had a headache the reporter asked for him to get a screening COVID test to make sure it was only a response to the vaccine and not something more serious. They were very surprised when his test results (both rapid and PCR) confirmed positive. The outcome of events was unknown.  Information about the Lot/batch number has been requested.
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 202104; Test Name: Covid-19 test; Test Result: Positive  ; Comments: his test results (both rapid and PCR) confirmed positive.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: leg weakness became worse; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable consumer. This is the second of 2 reports. A 71-year-old non-pregnant female patient received the second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Lot Number: EN6201) via an unspecified route of administration in right arm on 19Feb2021 at age of 71-year-old at single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Relevant medical history included COVID-19 from Nov2020 (Was in hospital with COVID in November. Did well in December and January). Other medical history reported as "none". No known allergies. Concomitant medications (received within 2 weeks of vaccination) included bupropion taken for an unspecified indication from an unspecified date; clonazepam taken for an unspecified indication from an unspecified date and "Celebs" (as reported). The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. The patient had not been tested for COVID-19 since the vaccination. The patient previously took the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Lot Number: EL9262) via an unspecified route of administration in left arm on 30Jan2021 at age of 71-year-old at single dose for COVID-19 immunisation and experienced "after first shot began experiencing weakness in legs" and "fell several times" on 01Feb2021. It reported after second shot leg weakness became worse. The event onset date after second shot was not reported. "Steroids" was considered as treatment for the event. CT scans of entire spine and brain with unknown result. The event resulted in Doctor or other healthcare professional office/clinic visit, Hospitalization (for 23 days), Disability or permanent damage. The outcome of the event was not recovered.; Sender's Comments: Linked Report(s) : US-PFIZER INC-2021476453 same patient/reporter/drug, different AE in separated time

SYMPTOM_TEXT: expired dose of IPOL was inadvertently administered/No AE; Initial information regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received on 26-Apr-2021 from a health care professional  This case involves a 13 year-old female patient who was inadvertently vaccinated with expired dose of IPV (VERO) [IPOL] (Expired product administered).   The patient's medical history, past medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided.  Concomitant medications included HPV VACCINE for prophylactic vaccination.  On 26-Apr-2021, the patient received third dose of suspect IPV (VERO) (Strength: standard; lot R1B251M and expiry date 13-Mar-2021) via an intramuscular route at an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  It was a case of actual medication error due to expired vaccine used (latency was on same day).  It was also reported that "caller with question on whether dose needed repetition. Caller also with question on any safety concern with administering expired dose".  At the time of report, no adverse event reported.  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holder's compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.

I took 2 more Alkseltzer Cold & Sinus (tylenol and decongestant) and got up.  3/29 3:30pm The headache and aches continue, I took 2 aleeve to manage the headache and body aches.  3/29 6:30pm the body aches and headache are better but not gone. She got her vaccine, she felt the burning sensation all the way down to her fingers and her wrist.  I proceeded to go forward and wait the 15 minutes.  She then started to have pain in the side of her neck on the right side, discomfort and pain in her arm.  Within the hour she started to have headaches (has had COVID in the past).  She went home and it was a nagging pain in her arm, not at the site but the whole arm was sore and limited using the arm due to the discomfort.  That night is when she came on the news and started that the vaccine was being pulled from administration.  That night it was like a pulling sensation right in her upper arm, up near the armpit and the fatty tissue from the breast and where you raise your arm.  When she started noticing the discoloration started in her skin.  Her hands started getting black, under both arms were black, the back of her legs was black, and she started feeling worsening fatigue.  She started getting worried and was looking at how her veins turned purple blue/green just in the one arm.  She was trying to figure out why she had limited use of her arm, and was holding it as if she had a sling on it as when it hung to her side it had the pulling sensation and a crawling sensation in her veins (that night and going into the next day).  The next morning she was so exhausted and tired, as was her mother who had the vaccine at the same time, and was not feeling well.  She was feeling that possibly due to the fibromyalgia she was have worsening symptoms than her mother.  She then started bruises on her body, on the arm itself as if somebody grabbed and squeezed her arm, purplish/black bruising.  It had her forearm develop 3 large pockets of swollen, almost as if the medicine was sitting in her arm.   She was slowly getting the pulling sensation down to her hand, and she called the UC first and due to the high volume of COVID she wanted to know how long of a wait she would have.  They instructed her to go to the ER due to the development of the blood clots on the news.  There was no change in her symptoms, and got to the point that she could not move her arm, and the knots stayed in there and there was a reddish discoloration around them.  Now she was having a pulling sensation in her chest and palpitations of pain near her heart.  She was having soreness in her legs to the point that she was not able to walk, and felt it was in her nerves 3 days after the vaccine.  She stayed in the bed the entire week just due to the exhaustion and effects.   Every time she would go to reach for something she would have the pulling sensation down to her hand, and the entire arm was swollen with the bruising all over.  Her body started having purple and blue knots and also in the left leg.  Her arm and fingers were swollen as well.  She then started having itching of her arm, and her lips started swelling and got up and went to Hospital and was able to be seen.  She was having problems with her stomach as well, having a knot in the stomach where it was protruding and started loosing weight since the vaccine.    The ER doctor told her she had a reaction to the vaccine, and did a Doppler to see if she had blood clots.  They did not give her the results and didn't feel that she didn't have problems.  She also went to the UC and back and forth to the ER, and still had the knots and finally looked at the knots and her jaw was swollen, and her arm was still swollen.  The UC told her that she was having a fibromyalgia flare.  She is still having the same symptoms green/blue and have started protruding.   Due to the fatigue she has mainly just stayed in bed and knew that she was to have COVID symptoms, but knows that the crawling sensation and the knots sitting in her arm, and now her arm looks disfigured and the swelling is not going down.  They told her that the test was negative for the blood clots.  She had made an appointment with her neurologist and has an APT on Tuesday 5/25/21.   She continues to loose weight no matter how much she consumes and still continues to have the knots and pain in the arm.
HISTORY: Fibromyalgia, neuropathy, sciatica, rheumatoid and psoriatic arthritis, sleep apnea, high blood pressure.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 10 minutes after receiving the vaccine, I felt tingling in my hands and feet. I reported it to the staff, and they consulted with each other before the nurse who gave me a shot came over and asked me more about it. She was surprised by it and said she hadn't seen that reaction before. She then googled and found it does sometimes happen. I was kept longer for observation and then went back to my office to eat and drink before getting on the road, thinking that might help. I figured it was just a temporary vaccine side effect and didn't think much about it at first, (Wondered if my reaction could have been pronounced since I had COVID in February.) But then the tingling symptoms didn't go away and came and went without a clear pattern. I have experienced them in both hands and feet; sometimes all extremities at once, sometimes just one or two -- on either side of the body or one extremity (a hand or a foot, sometimes more in the fingers, sometimes in the hand). While I may notice it more while I'm sitting, it doesn't go away when I walk. Then about a week or two after the vaccine (about a week or two ago), I started finding myself putting my hand to my lips or left side of my face because I felt slight numbness there. It started at my lips and a cm or inch spot around my left cheekbone, but more recently, it is my lips and a larger swath of my lower face. Always or almost always left side of my face. So here I am today, three weeks after the vaccine and I still (daily) feel tingly hands and/or feet and slight numbness on the left side of my face and lips. This is concerning to me and I am holding off on my 2nd vaccine until I can see a neurologist.
LAB_DATA: About a week ago, when the numbness in my face seemed to spread, I contacted my Dr. and asked if I should be seen by him or receive a referral to a neurologist. He set up a referral to Neurology. Unfortunately, due to their current patient load, I couldn't get an appointment until June 16. I can provide further information after that appointment and any tests run after that, if you can tell me how to submit that information.

Symptoms of weakness started about 6 weeks after influenza vaccine. Admitted to the hospital for altered mental status and weakness. Was diagnosed with axonal variant of Guillain-Barr� syndrome (acute motor and sensory axonal neuropathy), completed 5 days of therapeutic plasma exchange with improvement of motor function. Per the neurologist, it  is possible for patients to develop Guillain Barre syndrome 4 - 6 weeks after the influenza vaccine, but the true incidence is unknown and is difficult to prove it was the vaccine that triggered this syndrome. However, given the severity of his symptoms, the patient wanted us to report to VAERs just in case as he is a retired doctor.  Of note, the patient was hospitalized for other issues in addition to this (purpura with hematoma, heparin induced bleeding, systemic inflammatory syndrome) , so the hospitalization itself was not entirely due to the Guillain-Barre syndrome. Also, the patient had received the influenza vaccine many times in the past (gets it almost every year) and did not have this reaction.
HISTORY: BPH, HTN, atrial fibrillation, peripheral artery disease, hypothyroidism due to Hashimoto's thyroiditis

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PATIENT WAS NOT NERVOUS ABOUT RECEIVING HIS FIRST DOSE. OUR IMMUNIZATION CERTIFIED PHARMACY TECH ADMINISTERED THE DOSE. ABOUT 2 MINUTES LATER HE STATED HE WAS FEELING TINGLY AND HIS EAR TURNED A WHITE COLOR. THE TECHNICIAN CALLED ME INTO THE ROOM WHERE I EXAMINED THE PATIENT. HE WAS NOT RESPONDING AND HIS EYES WERE DILATED. HE WAS TRYING TO BREATH BUT HE WAS HAVING DIFFICULTY. WE MOVED HIM TO THE GROUND AND PLACED HIM ON HIS SIDE TO MAKE SURE HE DID NOT ASPERATE. AFTER ABOUT 20 SECONDS OF BEING ON THE GROUD HE STARTED BREATHING NORMALLY AND WAS CONSCIOUS. THE ENTIRE EPISODE LASTED ABOUT 1 MINUTE (MAYBE SLIGHLY LONGER). EMS ARRIVED A FEW MINUTES LATER. Administration Comments: Patient observed for 15 minutes then notified RN that she was starting to feel a tingling sensation on her tongue at 1717. Called provider and had MA bring vitals cart to conference room. PA presented to room. MA Sup brought vitals cart. BP at 1717 was 201/78 with a pulse of 58 and an O2 of 97. Patient states only her tongue is tingling. Denies SOB, chest pain, nausea/vomiting, trouble swallowing, vision changes or dizziness at this time. Had patient take her mask off and gave patient water. Patient denies feeling anxious but did run over to vaccine clinic for extra available dose of vaccine from across the street to receive vaccine. Patient appears flushed. States it is the end of tax season and she has been a little more stressed. Hx of COVID infection on 10/31/2020. Repeat BP at 1724, BP was 194/95, O2 99%, pulse 55. States it is only the sides of her tongue that feels tingly at this time. Denies hx of HTN, hx of anxiety. At 1726, states she is starting to feel tightness in her chest. States her tongue is getting better, is still oriented and talking. PA assessing patient. PA left at 1729 and requested that patient be observed for 30 more minutes. RN continues to stay with patient. Rechecked BP at that time and switched to R side for BP cuff, BP 203/83, pulse 58. Had MA get stethoscope. Assessed lungs and heart. Lungs sound clear bilaterally. Heart rate is regular. Radial pulses are present and regular. At 1735, patient states less chest tightness but now feels shaky. States she gets shaky when she goes through a high stress time. RN sat and talked with patient. Patient states she does feel like she was feeling a little anxious and worried of the unknown. Feels less tingling on her tongue now, just near the back near her molars. Denies dizziness, nausea/vomiting, numbness/tingling, vision changes, HA, chest pain, SOB, trouble swallowing. Pulse 54 per radial pulse. At 1750, BP 194/80, tightness gone, tingling improved. Denies any other symptoms at this time. Patient had been observed for 55 minutes after initial injection, provider back into room and assessed again. Plan for patient to follow up with her primary care provider within the next week. Reviewed signs and symptoms of when to seek ER care. Patient states her husband has a BP cuff at home and will check her BP daily. If she continues to have high BP, will go in to be seen sooner. If experiencing sypmtoms, will go to ER. Walked with patient to front door. Patient states she is still feeling good. Patient left building at 1800.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got her vaccine, no reaction to the arm, no arm pain, nothing.  Then that evening 3 hours later she could hardly walk when she stood up.  Her right side of her body starting from hip to inner thigh and stabbing pain in her groin area with any step she took.  Firing pain to her hip and inner thigh.  She was limping that evening and went to bed, and when she woke up with stabbing pain in her hip and groin area and unable to walk at all.  She had to scoop around in her office chair as she is OK to sit, but when she takes her first step on the right side has the stabbing pain until her body (warms) up for at least the first several steps at least.  She did go to her doctor and he prescribed Diclofenac sodium 75 mg twice daily for the inflammation and should go away within a week or two, but it has been almost a month and the symptoms have not gone away.  Her hip area has gotten much better, however, her groin area has gotten worse.  It's at the point that she can walk, but she grimaces and hurts once she's able to get up and walk.  In the right groin she can distinctly feel the sharp stabbing pain as she walks.  Again, as long as she's sitting she is okay, but upon trying to walk the first 5-6 steps it is painful.  The longer she walks the pain diminishes more.  She did not have these symptoms prior to the vaccine.   She did not fall or do anything to injure herself.  She is now going to restart taking the medication he prescribed to her.    First vaccine had foot pain on the right side that went away by the next day.
OTHER_MEDS: None at the time of vaccine.

Support staff checking in patients outside the building witnessed a patient passing out at the top of the walkway. One person ran inside to get the clinic coordinator.  She immediately asked staff to call EMS and she ran out to assess the situation.  The patient was lying on his side motionless.  She attempted to rouse the patient and assess if CPR was needed.  The patient opened his eyes and looked dazed and confused.  He rolled on his back.  He began to verbally respond and apologized for passing out.  He stated that this happens to him frequently when he gets an immunization or blood drawn.  He had abrasions and a small contusion on the left side of his face in the temple region with a small amount of blood and dirt from hitting the sidewalk. She was joined by NP and NP along with 2 medical assistants. While waiting to EMS to arrive, campus police came on the scene to help direct EMS whenever they arrived.   Vitals were taken BP 140/70  HR 62  2:30 PM .  An ice pack was applied to his head.  Additional information on the patient?s identity was acquired.  Patient was alert and oriented.  Patient had his cellphone and attempted to call his wife with no answer.  He also sent her a text.  EMS arrived on the scene.  Patient?s wife called and she apprised her of the situation as EMS assessed the patient.  After their examination, EMS declined to transport the patient due to the patient's narrative of this situation occurring frequently.  They advised him to follow-up with his MD and left the scene. Clinic staff and campus police stayed on the scene until the patient?s wife arrived.  She was advised to take him immediately to the ED to be assessed for a head injury.  Wife drove patient to hospital.   She called the patient later that evening.  Patient stated he was thoroughly examined for a potential head injury and was cleared.  He was given information on interventions he can try to use to avoid a severe vasovagal incident in the future.  Patient was cleared to get his second dose of COVID-19 vaccine.

For the first two weeks, there was only mild headache and fatigue.  But on day 12 (or 13) following the shot, my husband had severe abdominal pain and black, tarry poop. He had to crawl back to bed.  He continued to have severe  lightheadedness, shortness of breath, muscle aches, abdominal pain, and also ringing in his ears.  He called me early Saturday morning and told me what happened and that he called out from work.  (We do not live together. He is 280 miles away because of his job.) That man has called out sick only one time since I've met him in 1998; so when he told me he did not go to work, I knew it had to be really bad.  I drove up there ASAP the same day, and I took the pulse oximeter with me.  His oxygen levels were all over the place.  They were usually better (like high 70s to low 80s) while he was lying down.  When he would sit up or stand up, the number would plummet, reading so low I thought he was going to die. One time his finger was so cold that it took me 4 tries to get a reading.  It read at 55, but I realize that might be because his finger was too cold.

After my first shot on March 10, I had minor soreness around the injection site and fatigue the day following the injection.  After my second shot on April 6, I had minor soreness around the injection site, fatigue which lasted two days and low grade fever which I treated with one 400mg dose of ibuprofen.  I also developed a persistent high pitch "ringing" in my head/ears.  I believe it's what is know as tinnitus.  The volume on a range of 1(low) to 10(high) is 2/3 to 5/6.  For the first four weeks after my second shot, the ringing was constant and daily.  I noticed beginning week 5 that there would be days where it would completely stop or be barely noticeable.  The quiet periods ranged from a couple of hours to almost an entire day.  The quiet periods are generally begin in the mornings when I first get up. Otherwise they don't appear to follow a pattern.  I also noticed, if I consume alcohol it lessens or eliminates the ringing.
LAB_DATA: None -I contacted my doctor and he indicated he has not heard of tinnitus being a side effect of the covid vaccines and offered to refer me to an ENT.  I have not yet seen the ENT, but from everything I've read, there is no treatment or cure for tinnitus.  Fortunately it does not appear to have impacted my hearing.  I may ultimately consult a neurologist and ENT if this condition continues

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3 weeks after injection: Sudden onset of hearing loss in one ear, feeling of fullness/congestion in ear. Absolutely not a bacterial ear infection - no soreness/pain, redness, or discharge. Visited an ENT Dr. and inner ear issue confirmed. Hearing test showed significant loss or hearing (loudness) and loss of word discrimination.  Fri, 2-Apr: 1st COVID shot (Moderna). Slightly sore arm, no other symptoms/side-effects, all clear in 24 hrs. Fri, 23-Apr: Relatively rapid (over an hour or so) onset of hearing loss in left ear. Feeling of fullness in left ear, thought it might be congestion.  Sat, 24-Apr: No change/improvement in hearing of feeling of fullness in left ear. Sun, 25-Apr: I started to feel dizzy. I developed vertigo, though I did not get nauseous. Slept it off. Mon, 26-Apr: Awoke with no dizziness or vertigo. No change/improvement in hearing or feeling of fullness in left ear. Dizziness returned after dinner. Vertigo followed, more severe than the previous night. Unable to walk without help. Vomited and the nausea passed. Vertigo abated a bit, though still present. Slept it off. Tue, 27-Apr: Awoke with no dizziness or vertigo. No change/improvement in hearing of feeling of fullness in left ear Wed, 28-Apr: Saw ENT. First hearing test. Test confirmed quite a bit of hearing loss in left ear and some in the right ear. Thu, 29-Apr: 2nd COVID shot (Moderna). No side-effects until evening. Slight body ache, mild headache, maybe a mild fever. Some dizziness after eating. Fri, 30-Apr: Continued mild side-effects from COVID shot. Some dizziness after eating Sat, 1-May: Side-effects from COVID shot completely gone. Left ear noticeably worse. Sounds more attenuated, speech sounded more distorted. Sun, 2-May: No improvement in hearing Mon, 3-May: 2nd hearing test. Test confirmed significantly reduced hearing (volume) and speech recognition in left ear. Agreed to steroid injections to try to clear the suspected fluid retention/swelling. Tue: 4-May: 1st eardrum injection (10 mg dexamethasone) at 11:00 AM. No noticeable effect through bedtime. Wed, 5-May: Woke up with notably improved hearing in left ear (now only 10 or 20% attenuated). However, felt dizzy as soon as I woke up. Dizziness persisted until late afternoon. Thu, 6-May: No dizziness Fri, 7-May: 2nd eardrum injection (10 mg dexamethasone) at 11:30 AM. No noticeable effect through bedtime. Sat, 8-May: No improvement in left ear hearing, mildly dizzy when I woke up, dizziness persisted until late afternoon. Hearing not great in right ear over the course of the day (maybe 20% attenuated) Sun, 9-May: Minimal improvement in left ear hearing, if any. Right ear still partially impaired. A little light headed at times, no real dizziness. Mon, 10-May: Not dizzy when I woke up at 5:30 AM. Made a cup of coffee and ate an oat bran muffin at 6:15. Felt mildly dizzy by 6:30, persisted through the day and started to abate by evening. Tue, 11-May: No dizziness when I woke up. Hearing in left ear marginally improved. 3rd eardrum injection at 4:30 PM. Wed, 12-May: Woke up with improved hearing in left ear, still some attenuation, almost no distortion, still some feeling of fullness in the ear. No dizziness. Thu, 13-May: Woke up with hearing unchanged from Wed (i.e. no back-sliding). No dizziness in AM, though slightly lightheaded. Hearing degraded as the day progressed. Fri: 14-May: Woke up with hearing worse as compared to Thursday. Feeling of congestion/fullness in ears (more on the left than the right). Slightly lightheaded, no dizziness.
LAB_DATA: Multiple hearing tests confirmed loss of hearing.

As reported in the first dose: Symptoms appeared three days after second dose. I mainly have hissing perceived in my right ear, sometimes left ear, and sometimes in the middle of my head. The tone sometimes changes from hissing to a slight hum in both ears (like a faraway vacuum sound). After the second dose, I notice the humming sound is more prominent in my right ear, especially when I wear ear buds without accompanying music (such as wearing them when engaging in a phone conversation with someone).  Similar to the first dose, I get sudden spikes of my tinnitus that come out of nowhere but subside within a few seconds. The tinnitus is more prominent when in a silent room (such as sleeping at night), climbing the stairs, running, and after taking a shower. It sometimes gets worse if I am around loud noise.  I visited my primary care doctor for a routine physical exam on 5/7/21 and she didn't seem too concerned. She said there are many reasons for tinnitus and sometimes we don't know why it begins and I might not likely find a reason. She said she will refer me to an ENT if symptoms get worse or if I notice accompanying hearing loss.  I also do want to note I noticed hyperacusis (sensitivity to loud noise) approximately a week after my frst dose. That does seemed to have resolved itself just before the second dose (so it lasted about 2 weeks). I have not noticed hyperacusis after my second dose.
PRIOR_VAX: Same tinnitus after first dose of Pfizer

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA; I had an extreme adverse reaction that started a couple of hours after the shot: sore arm, vomiting, chills, fever, fatigue, muscle/body aches, and nausea. The Hospital gave me two bags of fluids for dehydration, nausea medicine, and did a full blood panel. I was discharged around 10:30 am. It took several days for me to start feeling better. However, about a week later, my left arm was still hurting and I developed a rash next to the injection location. The rash went away about two days later without treatment. About a week after that, my arm was still hurting so I called the urgent care and they recommended that I come in or wait it out, so I chose to wait it out and see if it got better. The pain did not go away, so I called the urgent care back and they made the appointment with my primary care doctor. My primary care doctor said my arm felt a little warm and he prescribed Voltren gel.  I used the gel and the pain did not stop, n fact it is now radiating down my arm and up my shoulder. If the pain does not go away by the end of this week, my doctor wants me to come in for further testing.

I received my 2nd shot of Moderna on April 27 and experienced what I believe were mild, common side effects for several days thereafter (fatigue, fever,  chills). On May 1, the vaccination side effects were finished, but I was stung by a wasp. The sting site was on my arm, 2-3 inches away from where the vaccine was injected.  The wasp sting became infected with puss developing immediately around the sting site and redness and itching spreading throughout the majority of my arm. I went to Urgent Care and was given a steroid injection in my glute, assigned to take Sulfamethoxazole-TMP, and told to return if symptoms worsened. The above mentioned symptoms worsened after 24 hours, so I returned to urgent care. I was given another steroid injection in my glute and assigned to take Prednisone for 3 days and Doxycycline for 10 days.  After completing the 10 days of Doxycycline, the infection appears to be finally healed and all pain/itching sensations are gone.  I am reporting this adverse effect to a wasp sting in case it has any relation to my immune response to the Moderna vaccine that immediately preceded it. I have been stung by bees (not wasps) numerous times in the past (as recently as 6 months ago) and never developed such an adverse reaction as this.
CUR_ILL: My adverse event report specifically relates to a reaction to a wasp sting immediately following vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received the vaccine and asked to sit down to wait for 15 minute observation period.  Pharmacy staff heard the patient fall and hit the ground. Pharmacist, reached patient first followed by pharmacist.  Patient was visualized on the ground with eyes open. Visualized the patient's neck bent backwards and muscles rigid including neck and arms.  Went to get cold compress while stayed with the patient.  At the same time, 911 was contacted by the pharmacy staff and a fire fighter in the pharmacy area was brought over to assist. Assisted the patient to a sitting position and noticed her pupils to be dilated. Returned with cold compress for neck and forehead. Went to get cold water while comforted the patient.  Fire fighters present took the patient's vitals and blood sugar and all was within normal limits.  Further questions with the patient found that she had not eaten breakfast or lunch that day.  She also indicated that she had passed out before at a concert while dehydrated in the past.  She had not passed out or reacted to any previous injections or vaccines.

She got her vaccine, she got very hot and sweaty within 10 minutes.  She was still filling out her form for the next vaccine.  She asked a paramedic some questions, and asked if anybody else had reported anybody get hot and sweaty and he directed her to go to the open door and drink some water and rest.  He asked if somebody could check her out, and came back again and asked again and they hooked her up to some electrodes and called the ambulance (somewhat foggy memory).  She was having a lot of palpitations which included PVC's, and possibly other heart arrhythmias at the same time.  He got to the hospital and could tell that she was going to the trauma room and they were waiting on her.  She had an Echocardiogram which showed that her left bundle branch was not working, her Troponin's were going up and went from very low  to high and then started trending down again.  She had a cardiac cath and was told that she had nothing wrong with her heart and had a heart of a child.   They mentioned Takotsubo's cardiomyopathy and wanted to do another in 6-8 weeks, which she had done and it is totally back to normal.   Her blood pressure was fluctuant between high and low. I awoke on April 5th at 6 am.  I was deaf in both ears except the sound of my own saliva in the right ear.  Upon attempting to rise I was exceedingly dizzy/light-headed.  I went to the ground and then extreme loud - extremely loud sound in head.  I held my head in my hands and attempted to stand again and could not.  Finally I was able to stand and get myself to the bathroom.  The loud sound and deafness continued for about 20 to 30 minutes at that intensity, then lessened.  Was back to "normal" about an hour later, except fullness in right ear.  I really should have called 911, yet I was in a rural area with my 99 year old mother and did not want to startle her.  One week later, April 13th, tinnitus, lower volume, and vertigo returned.  Vertigo was intermittent; tinnitus has been 24/7 since April 13th.  I saw ENT, on April 7th.  He thought I either had a stroke or a vestibular migraine, yet he was not aware of the 24/7 tinnitus.  He ordered MRI.  Results negative for stroke or tumor.  I have an appointment with ENT next week. (Was visiting my mom and family at time of initial acute onset.)

Eye?s were dilated, he was diaphoretic, zoned out and not responding initially to voice, but eyes were open. Eventually got patient up to a wheelchair and taken to office area to lay down and monitor. Father was notified and sat with us after he arrived at the school. Patient drank 1 full 120cc orange juice and approximately 6oz of water. Throughout monitoring patient gradually felt better. Pupils corrected to normal, wasn?t diaphoretic anymore, and vitals improved. He stated this has happened before with lab draws and shots, but not this severe. Writer and colleagues informed him to notify people that are going to give him shots or lab draws about his history. Also informed him to notify his teachers if he feels anything out the ordinary for the rest of the day. Make sure he hydrates. Patient then sat up and walked in the room. He stated he felt fine like before getting the shot. Patient left stable and under his own power.
PRIOR_VAX: reports passing out but not that severe

He received the COVID vaccine 5 days ago in the afternoon and initially had what he expected to be normal side effects from the vaccine that evening. Symptoms included body aches, runny nose and general malaise. However, over the last few days he has felt worse and developed more congestion, cough, and sweating. He did improve a little bit 2 days ago but then started to feel worse yesterday and had a worsening cough that is resulting in some chest tightness. Cough is productive sounding. Mom describes it as barking. No appreciable wheezing but he sounds hoarse. He has some SOB after coughing repeatedly. He states it simply feels like it is hard to breathe for 10-20minutes after a coughing attack but then it resolves. He developed sweating yesterday as well. He states he will just start sweating for no reason. No measured fever. No chills. Today he has dried skin and cracked lips from blowing/wiping his nose all the time. No fevers. No vomiting. Pt is a 45 y/o F who presents w/ epigastic pain and intermittent L arm numbness. She was found to have extensive clots in descending thoracic aorta with additional clot in  L subclavian and axillary arteries.   She denies any birth control and does not smoke. We have a hypercoaguable workup pending. Transthoracic echo 5/13 did not reveal a cardiac source nor PFO.   She developed sx and saw PCP 4/6/21 which was 3d after second dose COVID vaccine, Moderna (administered 4/3/21). At the PCP 4/6 pt complained of some left arm numbness and a decreased pulse and the doctor noted that it was a little bit cooler to touch and ordered a arterial ultrasound and MRI of the brain.  However, the patient did not feel like she needed it therefor did not have either test done.   During her admission the pt has been evaluated by vascular surgery and cardiothoracic surgery. Surgically the patient is to have 5/14/21 Penumbra thrombectomy of L axillary and L subclavian artery. Then she will have 5/17/21 removal of thrombus in descending thoracic aorta via L thoracotomy/L heart bypass.

I have broken out in full body hives that have not gone away in six weeks. They started a week after my first vaccine, with a mild breakout I initially did not attribute to the vaccine because it started on my scalp and  it wasn't localized to my arm where the vaccine injection was, which is the only reaction I'd read about online. However after my 2nd dose, a week to the day, they flarred up again all over my neck and chest and abdomen and have not left since, but only spread, even with a steroid shot given at an after hours urgent clinic, a week long treatment of steroids, and a slower 3 week treatment of steroids, claritin, zyrtec, and benadryl.   The hives are not responding to the steroid prednisone or your typical over the counter antihistamines. They are on my scalp, face, neck, chest, abdomen, groin, and upper thighs. They are red and tend to swell and connect together. It's very typical of erythema multiforme. When not on the steroid my hands also swell and itch/burn which is very painful. I have been to the dermatologist twice and seen my PCP twice and they all agree given no other known allergies or exposure to new/unusual household contaminents that this is a vaccine allergic response my body is having.

I have experienced an increased amount of Afib following my Moderna covid-19 vaccinations. I used to be able to expect at least two weeks Afib free between episodes, but on the evening of my first shot on March 12th I had Afib only four days after a typical episode. Then again on March 22nd and 30th.  On April 8th I had my second Moderna dose. On April 11th I had Afib again and didn't think that much of it being related to the shot as I had been fever free for over a day at that time. But with episodes on the 13th, 14th, 17th, 18th, 20th(3 episodes) of April that far surpass the frequency of Afib in my history, I have become quite suspicious of the shots as the trigger. The episodes have thankfully been shorter than in the past, some ending within 15 minutes and some as long as four hours. My historical events had often lasted 12 to 18 hours. The arrhythmia events have significantly subsided with only one  three minute arrythmia (likely flutter) in the last 12 days and less short duration palpitations as well.

patient reported to nurse  within 5 minutes of being vaccinated that she had 'soreness and pressure' in her throat. She denied difficulty breathing with no other symptoms and Clinical Leader was notified. She was taken to the triage area for further monitoring and evaluation with CL. She maintained verbal ability during the observation period, and at no time reported difficulty breathing. No urticaria was observed; no itching or gi symptoms reported by patient during interaction. Patient was asked to lie down with her feet up which she declined, and was seated in a chair during triage. Vitals remained stable during her observation and she was encouraged to take liquids and given some water. She denied eating lunch as well, and appeared possibly anxious due to her symptoms. Clinical Leader asked her to remove her mask for optimal breathing, which appeared to lessen  anxiety in addtion to the supportive care provided. Clinic Medical Director was informed and in agreement with observation. She was observed for over an hour, at which time her symptoms continued to improve and vitals remained stable. Pt did not have an adverse event, but there was a temperature excursion of the J &  J vaccine vial. Vaccine was taken out of fridge at 12:03pm, then 1 dose drawn up at around 12:11pm. I then accidentally left the vial out at room temperature for around 35 minutes. At this point I then put the vial back in the fridge. I asked a couple other pharmacists if okay to use and they said yes, so I drew up more doses around 3:30pm (this is an estimate). I administered this particular dose shortly after drawing up. All doses were administered within the 6 hour timeframe. Per conversation w/ manufacturer the vial was out at room temperature longer than what is suggested (i.e. probably around 5 minutes longer than it should have been out of fridge), so the representative at the mfr is sending this to the safety team to find out if re-vaccination may be necessary.
